<p>Vancouver's marine climate requires HVAC systems that can efficiently handle moderate heating needs in winter and cooling requirements during summer months. Heat pumps are particularly well-suited for this climate, as they can provide both heating and cooling efficiently when temperatures rarely drop below freezing. For Vancouver homes, heat pumps with SEER ratings of 16-20 and HSPF ratings of 9-10 offer optimal efficiency. Gas furnaces paired with central air conditioning units should have AFUE ratings of at least 90% and SEER ratings of 16 or higher to maximize energy savings.</p>

